ganga/python/Ganga
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- hotfix release for the broken jobs repository for jobs that were created with Ganga 5.8.7 and then
tried to be used in Ganga 5.8.8

- with the new Ganga version 5.8.9 the user has to start Ganga and then restart it to get the
repository (for the broken jobs) rebuilt and the jobs reloaded properly. If the user starts Ganga
(but doesn't restart it) and tries to access a broken job he will get a message like this

RegistryKeyError: The object #269 in registry 'jobs' could not be accessed - Please restart Ganga in
order to reload the object!

After restarting, all broken jobs should load and should be accessible


